      {
        "type": "assistantMessage",
        "message": {
          "text": "## Deliverable: `sim-p0-md-lj-li-parity`\n\n**PR:** https://github.com/li-langverse/lic/pull/179  \n**Branch:** `cursor/sim-algo-plan-loop` (pushed at `0305ba5`)\n\n### What was fixed\n\nTier-2 `md_lennard_jones` Li builds were marked `li_pure` while `li/main.li` was a parallel-for stub, so the harness saw no `LI_PRINT_SINK_F64` output and verify failed.\n\n**Fix (commit `ca47b53`):**\n1. **`benchmarks/tier2_physics/md_lennard_jones/li/main.li`** — Driver calls `li_md_kernel()` then `li_rt_volatile_sink_f64(li_md_checksum())` over shared `md_core.c` via `LI_EXTRA_C`.\n2. **`benchmarks/harness/bench.py`** — Removed erroneous `li_pure=True` on MD so Li links the same C kernel as native/cpp.\n3. **Scoped peers** — Same sink pattern on `heat_equation_2d`, `three_body`, `nbody_gravity`, `double_pendulum` so `li-sim-scientific` package gates pass together.\n\n**Li vs native checksum:** `0.6892536936825765` (match)\n\n### Files changed (core)\n\n| Path | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `benchmarks/tier2_physics/md_lennard_jones/li/main.li` | Runtime sink + shared-kernel driver |\n| `benchmarks/harness/bench.py` | Drop `li_pure` on MD |\n| `benchmarks/tier2_physics/{heat_equation_2d,three_body,nbody_gravity,double_pendulum}/li/main.li` | Align sink pattern |\n| `docs/reports/sim-plan/algos/md_lennard_jones.md` | Iteration notes (`implemented_smoke: true`) |\n| `docs/ecosystem/sim-agent-handoff.md`, `sim-algorithm-backlog.md` | Status updates |\n\n### Tests / gates run\n\n```bash\nexport CC=clang-22 CXX=clang++-22\n./scripts/build.sh\n./scripts/sim-plan-gates.sh\n# includes:\n#   bench_sim.py --package li-sim-scientific\n#   bench.py --verify-results --tier 2 --package li-sim-scientific\n#   bench-package.sh li-sim-scientific --timing\n#   sim-bench-memory.sh\n```\n\nAll gates **passed** on this run. Scoped Li wall time for MD ≈ 1.16s (on par with cpp/rust/julia).\n\n### Follow-up (out of scope)\n\nPure-Li MD kernel (no `LI_EXTRA_C`) remains a separate Wave B item; this slice restores harness parity via the reference C kernel only."
        }
